37133,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Graves: Plastering, writing, and sitting on graves","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 11, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, prohibited plastering over graves, writing upon them, building over them, and treading upon them. Al-Tirmidhi said, \"Some of the scholars granted a concession, among them Al-Hasan al-Basri, to put clay over the graves. Al-Shafi'i said: There is nothing wrong with\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2903,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/16\/la-qabr-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":37133,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Graves: Do not turn homes into graves, or graves into celebrations","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 16, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not turn your houses into graves, and do not turn my grave into a place of festivity. Send blessings upon me, for your blessings will reach me wherever you are.\" Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 2042\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21173,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/11\/11\/graves-desecrating-dead\/","url_meta":{"origin":37133,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Graves: Desecrating the dead like harming the living","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 11, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBreaking the bones of a dead person is like breaking them when he is alive.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 3207 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0631\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37185,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/10\/19\/visiting-graves-softens-heart\/","url_meta":{"origin":37133,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Graves: Visiting the dead softens the heart","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 19, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cI had prohibited you from visiting the graves, but it occurred to me that now you may visit them. Verily, they soften the heart, shed tears in the eyes, and remind of the Hereafter. Thus, visit them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35519,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/03\/prophet-prays-servant\/","url_meta":{"origin":37133,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Funerals: The Prophet prays for a humble mosque servant","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 3, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: A black woman, or a young man, used to maintain the mosque and one day the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, missed her and asked about her. They said, \u201cShe has died.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cYou would not announce it to me?\u201d It\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12293,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/18\/graves-not-sit-pray\/","url_meta":{"origin":37133,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Graves: Do not sit on graves, do not pray to them","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 18, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Marthad reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not sit upon the graves and do not pray towards them.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 972 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064e\u0631\u0652\u062b\u064e\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u063a\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0648\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0644\u0650\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u